$:/plugins/ScottSauyet/FiraCode/readme.text: This plugin simply embeds [[Fira Code|https://github.com/tonsky/FiraCode]] in a Tiddlywiki. Fira Code is a monospaced font with programming ligatures. This means that certain combinations of symbols are shown as cleaner characters. For instance * @@color: #dd1144;background-color: #f7f7f9;border: 1px solid #e1e1e8;padding: 0 3px 2px;border-radius: 3px;font-family: "SFMono-Regular",Consolas,"Liberation Mono",Menlo,Courier,monospace; <= @@ becomes `<=` * @@color: #dd1144;background-color: #f7f7f9;border: 1px solid #e1e1e8;padding: 0 3px 2px;border-radius: 3px;font-family: "SFMono-Regular",Consolas,"Liberation Mono",Menlo,Courier,monospace; --> @@ becomes `-->` * @@color: #dd1144;background-color: #f7f7f9;border: 1px solid #e1e1e8;padding: 0 3px 2px;border-radius: 3px;font-family: "SFMono-Regular",Consolas,"Liberation Mono",Menlo,Courier,monospace; 0xFF @@ becomes `0xFF` * @@color: #dd1144;background-color: #f7f7f9;border: 1px solid #e1e1e8;padding: 0 3px 2px;border-radius: 3px;font-family: "SFMono-Regular",Consolas,"Liberation Mono",Menlo,Courier,monospace; 8.5x11 @@ becomes `8.5x11` * @@color: #dd1144;background-color: #f7f7f9;border: 1px solid #e1e1e8;padding: 0 3px 2px;border-radius: 3px;font-family: "SFMono-Regular",Consolas,"Liberation Mono",Menlo,Courier,monospace; => @@ becomes `=>` !! Sample This Javascript code is written just with the symbols on a standard keyboard. But it displays a number of more readable symbols. If you copy and paste this to another editor, you will get back the symbols as typed. ```javascript // clampit :: Functor f, Ord a => a -> a -> f a -> f a const clampit = (lo, hi) => (xs) => map(x => x <= lo ? lo : x >= hi ? hi : x, xs) const threeToSeven = clampit(3, 7) threeToSeven([8, 6, 7, 5, 3, 0, 9]) //~> [7, 6, 7, 5, 3, 3, 7] threeToSeven(Just(1)) //~> Just(3) threeToSeven(Just(5)) //~> Just(5) threeToSeven(Just(13)) //~> Just(7) threeToSeven(Nothing()) //~> Nothing() clampit('c', 'p')('capital').join('') //~> "ccpipcl" ``` !! All Ligatures [img[$:/plugins/ScottSauyet/FiraCode/all_ligatures.png]]

$:/plugins/ScottSauyet/FiraCode/usage.title: $:/plugins/ScottSauyet/FiraCode/usage
$:/plugins/ScottSauyet/FiraCode/usage.text:
!! Using the plugin for all `code` sections

If you are using the default theme, you can update `$:/ControlPanel > Appearance > Theme Tweaks > Settings > Code Font` to include `"Fira Code"`, as the first or only entry in the list.  Equivalently, you can update the shadow tiddler, [[$:/themes/tiddlywiki/vanilla/settings/codefontfamily]] to begin with `"Fira Code"`.

If you are using a different theme, you may be able to set it the same way, or you can set the font for `code` blocks to `"Fira Code"`, by creating a `text/css` tiddler tagged `$:/tags/Stylesheet` with this CSS:

```css
code {
    font-family: "Fira Code"
}
```

----------

!! Using the plugin inline

You can wrap any section of text in `@@css ... @@` blocks, like this:

```
@@font-family: "Fira Code"; const nonNegatives = (ns) => ns.filter(n => n >= 0) @@
```

to yield something like this:

> @@font-family: "Fira Code"; const nonNegatives = (ns) => ns.filter(n => n >= 0) @@

----------

!! Or however

With this plugin installed, you simply have [[Fira Code|https://github.com/tonsky/FiraCode]] available to you.  Use it how you like.
